class DependencyTracker: Track dependencies during execution
TEST = '<test>'
__enter__(self) -> Any: Track entering an if/while/for block
__exit__(self, exc_type:Type, exc_value:BaseException, traceback:traceback) -> Union[bool, NoneType]: Track exiting an if/while/for block
__init__(self, *args:Any, **kwargs:Any) -> None: Constructor. Arguments are passed to DataTracker.__init__()

get(self, name:str, value:Any) -> Any: Track a read access for variable `name` with value `value`

dependencies(self) -> __main__.Dependencies: Return dependencies
ignore_location_change(self) -> None
ignore_next_location_change(self) -> None

class DataTracker: Track data accesses during execution
__enter__(self) -> Any: Enter `with` block. To be overloaded in subclasses.
__exit__(self, exc_type:Type, exc_value:BaseException, traceback:traceback) -> Union[bool, NoneType]: Exit `with` block. To be overloaded in subclasses.
__init__(self, log:bool=False) -> None: Constructor. If `log` is set, turn on logging.

arg(self, value:Any, pos:Union[int, NoneType]=None, kw:Union[str, NoneType]=None) -> Any: Track `value` being passed as argument. `pos` (if given) is the argument position (starting with 1). `kw` (if given) is the argument keyword.
augment(self, name:str, value:Any) -> Any: Track augmenting `name` with `value`. To be overloaded in subclasses.
call(self, func:Callable) -> Callable: Track a call to `func`.
get(self, name:str, value:Any) -> Any: Track getting `value` from `name`.

param(self, name:str, value:Any, pos:Union[int, NoneType]=None, vararg:str='', last:bool=False) -> Any: At the beginning of a function, track parameter `name` being set to `value`. `pos` is the position of the argument (starting with 1). `vararg` is "*" if `name` is a vararg parameter (as in *args), and "**" is `name` is a kwargs parameter (as in *kwargs). `last` is True if `name` is the last parameter.
ret(self, value:Any) -> Any: Track `value` being used as return value.
set(self, name:str, value:Any, loads:Union[Set[str], NoneType]=None) -> Any: Track setting `name` to `value`.
test(self, cond:_ast.AST) -> _ast.AST: Test condition `cond`. To be overloaded in subclasses.
class Dependencies: A dependency graph
FONT_NAME = 'Fira Mono, Courier, monospace'
NODE_COLOR = 'peachpuff'

__init__(self, data:Union[Dict[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]], Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]], NoneType]=None, control:Union[Dict[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]], Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]], NoneType]=None) -> None: Create a dependency graph from `data` and `control`. Both `data` and `control` are dictionaries holding _nodes_ as keys and sets of nodes as values. Each node comes as a tuple (variable_name, location) where `variable_name` is a string and `location` is a pair (function, lineno) where `function` is a callable and `lineno` is a line number denoting a unique location in the code.
__repr__(self) -> str: Represent dependencies as a Python expression
__str__(self) -> str: Return string representation of dependencies
_repr_svg_(self) -> Any: If the object is output in Jupyter, render dependencies as a SVG graph
all_vars(self) -> Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]: Return a set of all variables (as `var_name`, `location`) in the dependencies

backward_slice(self, *criteria:Union[str, Tuple[Callable, int], Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]], mode:str='cd', depth:int=-1) -> __main__.Dependencies: Create a backward slice from nodes `criteria`. `mode` can contain 'c' (draw control dependencies) and 'd' (draw data dependencies) (default: 'cd')

code(self, *items:Callable, mode:str='cd') -> None: List `items` on standard output, including dependencies as comments. If `items` is empty, all included functions are listed. `mode` can contain 'c' (draw control dependencies) and 'd' (draw data dependencies) (default: 'cd').
graph(self) -> graphviz.dot.Digraph: Draw dependencies.
_code(self, item:Callable, mode:str) -> None
_source(self, node:Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str
add_hierarchy(self, g:graphviz.dot.Digraph) -> graphviz.dot.Digraph: Add invisible edges for a proper hierarchy.
draw_dependencies(self, g:graphviz.dot.Digraph) -> None
expand_criteria(self, criteria:List[Union[str, Tuple[Callable, int], Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]]) -> List[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]: Return list of vars matched by `criteria`.
format_var(self, var:Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]], current_func:Union[Callable, NoneType]=None) -> str: Return string for `var` in `current_func`.
id(self, var:Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str: Return a unique ID for `var`.
label(self, var:Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str: Render node `var` using HTML style.
make_graph(self, name:str='dependencies', comment:str='Dependencies') -> graphviz.dot.Digraph
repr_dependencies(self, vars:Dict[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]], Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]]) -> str
repr_deps(self, var_set:Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]) -> str
repr_var(self, var:Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str
source(self, node:Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str: Return the source code for a given node.
tooltip(self, var:Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str: Return a tooltip for node `var`.
validate(self) -> None: Perform a simple syntactic validation of dependencies
